{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":107224,"duration_api_ms":162874,"num_turns":5,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"ddfeea7d-24ea-4046-badd-4c394c2aa76e","total_cost_usd":0.45851295000000014,"usage":{"input_tokens":4,"cache_creation_input_tokens":28348,"cache_read_input_tokens":79754,"output_tokens":3235,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":28348,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":1011,"outputTokens":10048,"cacheReadInputTokens":443787,"cacheCreationInputTokens":51949,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.16056594999999999,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000},"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":4,"outputTokens":3235,"cacheReadInputTokens":79754,"cacheCreationInputTokens":28348,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.297947,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"summary":"Assessed all four amendments against the actual codebase. Two are clear bugs (fr-9-170e6cf9 and fr-9-84798097) where error classifications are lost or inconsistent, causing retryable treatment of terminal failures. One (fr-9-466cef86) is a valid latency concern with the initial 5s backoff. One (fr-9-2de499b0) is a reasonable maintainability suggestion but not a correctness issue in the current single-callsite design.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-9-2de499b0","decision":"reject","rationale":"The observation is factually accurate: spawn_and_wait() returns the timeout error without calling preserve_failed_artifacts(), and that call happens in invoke(). However, invoke() is currently the only call site for spawn_and_wait(), and the cleanup contract is correctly implemented there. The amendment is framed around a hypothetical future call site that doesn't handle Timeout specially. Moving cleanup into spawn_and_wait() would actually be wrong — spawn_and_wait() doesn't own the PreparedCommand and shouldn't be responsible for artifact preservation. The current layering (spawn_and_wait handles process lifecycle, invoke handles artifact lifecycle) is sound. Adding a doc comment on the cleanup contract is fine but doesn't warrant an amendment-level change."},{"amendment_id":"fr-9-466cef86","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified in engine.rs:4620 that backoff_for_attempt(cursor.attempt) is called with the current attempt (1) before cursor.retry() increments it, producing a 5-second delay on the very first retry. The backoff_for_attempt function returns base * 2^(attempt-1), so attempt=1 yields the full 5s base. For transient JSON parse errors or partial-response failures that would succeed immediately, this adds gratuitous latency. Using attempt-1 (which maps to 0 → ZERO by the function's own guard) for the first retry is a standard pattern and would cut p50 retry latency for the common single-transient-failure case without affecting the exponential ramp on repeated failures."},{"amendment_id":"fr-9-170e6cf9","decision":"accept","rationale":"Confirmed in service.rs:383-408 that map_invoke_error's catch-all 'other' arm converts every non-Invocation* error — including BackendUnavailable — into InvocationFailed { failure_class: TransportFailure }. This discards the BinaryNotFound classification that openrouter_backend.rs:68-77 and process_backend.rs:789-800 carefully set. The result: invoke-time BackendUnavailable{BinaryNotFound} gets treated as retryable TransportFailure, burning through all retry attempts before failing. This is a real correctness bug — the map_invoke_error function needs a BackendUnavailable arm that preserves (or maps) the failure_class metadata."},{"amendment_id":"fr-9-84798097","decision":"accept","rationale":"Confirmed three defects in process_backend.rs:802-808: (1) std::env::var returns Ok(\"\") for a blank OPENROUTER_API_KEY, which passes the check and sends an empty key to the API — failing later with an unhelpful transport error; (2) the error class is TransportFailure (retryable), directly contradicting check_availability() at lines 1200-1208 which uses BinaryNotFound (terminal) for the same condition; (3) the test at process_backend_test.rs:1394-1421 asserts InvocationFailed, encoding the incorrect behavior. The fix is straightforward: mirror the check_availability logic (.unwrap_or_default().is_empty()) and return BackendUnavailable{BinaryNotFound}, then update the test expectation."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"7e0be9d8-9c79-4bb8-8597-e76f06486445"}
